column2: Google parent Alphabet Inc. reported quarterly results that exceeded Wall Street estimates Tuesday, initially propelling shares up 8% in after-hours trading. The company's board also announced a 20-for-1 stock split.
column4: Alphabet shares pop 8% on big earnings beat, 20-for-1 stock split

column2: The Google parent reported fourth-quarter sales of $75.3 billion, up 32% year over year. The company also announced a 20-for-one stock split.
column4: Alphabet Stock Is Soaring on an Earnings Beat. The Company Is Finally Splitting Its Stock, Too.
